sp.p:
 Well, mayst thou have the Spirit of persuasion;

and he the ears of profiting, that what thou speakest,

may move; and what he hears may be believed, that the

true Prince, may (for recreation sake) prove a false thief;

for the poor abuses of the time, want countenance. Farewell, you shall find me in Eastcheape.

 Strike down with them, cut the villains throats;

a whoreson Caterpillars: Bacon-fed Knaves, they hate us

youth; down with them, fleece them.
